title: The benefits of data quality action plans
Why use data quality action plans?
Course content
body: This course contains two modules and will introduce you to the fundamentals of good data quality assessments.

title: What does a good assessment look like?
displayTitle: What does a good assessment look like?
body: Any assessment of quality is better than none. But assessing the right things in the right ways will make your assessments more effective.

title: Why do we assess data quality?
displayTitle: Why do we assess data quality?
body: Conducting data quality assessments can seem daunting or time consuming, but they can provide great benefits in the long term.

title: Assessing data quality
body:
A data quality action plan (DQAP) is one way to manage data quality assessments. As we explored in the previous module, however you choose to assess data quality, you must ensure that your approach is:

  • Evidence based
  • Linked to purpose
  • Proactive
  • Communicated

title: What are data quality action plans?
displayTitle: What are data quality action plans?

title: What are the benefits?
body: There are many benefits to data quality action plans that are not always part of traditional data quality assessments.

title: What is a data quality action plan?
displayTitle: What is a data quality action plan?

title: What is data quality?
body: In government we use data in lots of different ways. Sometimes we say that data is good quality or bad quality, but it is not that simple. The quality of the data can vary by the way it is used, so the quality will not be the same for everyone.

title: Coming up next
body:
This module has looked at what data quality means, why it needs to be assessed, and what makes a good data quality assessment. 

In the next module, we will introduce Data Quality Action Plans as a possible assessment method. We will explore what they are, and why they can be a good way to improve data quality in your organisation.

title: Why are data quality actions plans effective?
displayTitle: Why are data quality actions plans effective?
body: Traditional data quality assessments are comprehensive, but data quality actions plans can be much more effective.

title: The benefits of data quality action plans
displayTitle: The benefits of data quality action plans
body: Data quality action plans have some things in common with traditional assessments, as well as some differences. There are many potential benefits to using data quality action plans over traditional data quality assessments.

title: How do you feel about data quality?
displayTitle: How do you feel about data quality?
body: This module looks at how to conduct good data quality assessments. Before we learn more, let's reflect on how confident you already are that you know how to achieve this.
